  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman has received Elizur Wright&apos;s note and must reply in the negative to the questions in the letter. Chapman has written a number of letters to Elizur Wright, but has finally resolved not to send them. She asks if Mr. Williams can get a package, sent by the ladies of Glasgow, from the Custom House.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman wrote the following postscript in the margin: &quot;Tell brother [Henry B.] Stanton that (to use one of his own felicitous expressions) &apos;we are taking the starch out of the sanctified linen&apos; by the dozen.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
